# WHAT IT IS
#   Fusion is a multi-target source-to-source transpiled language
#   designed for implementing reusable library components from a
#   single .fu codebase that emits human-readable, dependency-free,
#   idiomatic code in every supported target language —
#   *no* shared runtime, *no* virtual machine, *no* emulation
#   layer, *no* per-target bindings.  Translation produces
#   target-native naming conventions (PascalCase methods become
#   `snake_case` for Python, `camelCase` for JavaScript /
#   TypeScript / Swift / Java, etc.) and emits idiomatic
#   target-language documentation comments inline.  Existing
#   downstream uses include the recoil-rs gameboy emulator core,
#   the asap audio cross-platform decoder library, the FAILE
#   compression library, plus several long-running cross-platform
#   library projects maintained by the upstream author.
#
#   The toolchain is a single multi-target binary `fut` that
#   takes one or more `.fu` source files plus a target spec
#   (either explicit via `-l <LANG>` or implicit via the
#   `.<ext>,<ext>,…` extension list of the `-o FILE` argument)
#   and emits one output file per target language.  Targets:
#     c | cpp | cs | d | java | js | py | swift | ts | d.ts | cl
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from Fut.java `usage()`,
#                       extracted via `gh api repos/fusionlanguage
#                       /fut/contents/Fut.java`)
#
#   Usage: fut [OPTIONS] -o FILE INPUT.fu...
#
#   Translation options:
#     -l c                           Translate to C
#     -l cpp                         Translate to C++
#     -l cs                          Translate to C#
#     -l d                           Translate to D
#     -l java                        Translate to Java
#     -l js                          Translate to JavaScript
#     -l py                          Translate to Python
#     -l swift                       Translate to Swift
#     -l ts                          Translate to TypeScript
#     -l d.ts                        Translate to TypeScript
#                                    declarations
#     -l cl                          Translate to OpenCL C
#
#   File / naming options:
#     -o FILE                        Write to the specified file
#                                    (also accepts a multi-target
#                                    extension list:
#                                    `-o out.c,cpp,cs,d,java,js,
#                                    py,swift,ts,cl` emits all
#                                    targets at once)
#     -n NAME                        Specify C++/C# namespace,
#                                    Java package, or C name
#                                    prefix
#     -D NAME                        Define a conditional
#                                    compilation symbol
#                                    (`#if NAME` / `#endif`
#                                    pre-processor)
#     -r FILE.fu                     Read the specified source
#                                    file but don't emit code
#                                    for it  (used for shared
#                                    library headers that should
#                                    be visible to the type
#                                    checker but emitted only by
#                                    a separate invocation)
#     -I DIR                         Add directory to resource
#                                    search path  (controls
#                                    where `resource()` /
#                                    `resourceLength()` /
#                                    `readResource()` calls find
#                                    their backing files)
#
#   Help / version:
#     --help                         Display this information
#     --version                      Display version information
#                                    (`Fusion Transpiler 3.3.3
#                                    (Java)` / `(C++)` / `(C#)`
#                                    depending on which
#                                    bootstrap host was built)
#
